programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Bummed Out To Belle Of The Ball
programme.desc: Jennifer has been feeling older since her back injury six months ago. Her job requires shopping in Beverly Hills and attending charity balls in appropriate attire. But at six feet tall, size 16 and on a budget, this is no easy task. She needs a makeover!
programme.sub-title: From Bummed Out To Belle Of The Ball

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Saying "I Do" To A New Look
programme.desc: Driving a big rig over two million miles and being a single dad have taken a huge toll on Michael's appearance. But major dental prosthetics and state-of-the-art dermatology bring out his softer side, then it's up to the Glam Squad to find a new look!
programme.sub-title: Saying "I Do" To A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Tony Goodwin "One Year On"
programme.desc: We revisit Midlands' band promoter Tony Goodwin who's poll of one hundred people last year suggested he was a colossal thirteen years older than he actually was.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Mom's Day Out
programme.desc: Nancy is a mother who's almost out of gas and in need of a rejuvenating jump-start. The glam squad breathes life into Nancy's fashion sense and provides this over-worked parent some relief from her frazzled life.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jayne English
programme.desc: Can Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her illustrious team of experts turn back time for 41-year-old Jayne English who went from a size 22 to a size 10 in just 18 months?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Nerys McGarry
programme.desc: Can the team pull off their biggest challenge to date and make Nerys McGarry - who has lost eight stone - 21 years younger?

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is looking after a sick and orphaned baby elephant called Togo. However, despite Evan and Du Plessis' constant vigil, Togo is dying from a broken heart. Evan is distraught and Du Plessis promises they will look after her together.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Sarah's absence couldn't have come at a worse time for Leopard's Den. Nature Conservation is carrying out their annual inspection and everything has to be tip top. Danny's determined they pass with flying colours and everyone is roped in to help.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Trevanions are delighted when Fatani asks Danny to take an aggressive hippo off his hands. As they prepare for its arrival Sarah gets a bit of a shock when her mother Caroline beats the hippo to the post.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Business is looking up at Leopard's Den but Sarah is feeling agitated. Caroline thinks it because Simon, her ex husband and Evan and Olivia's Dad, is arriving from England to get married. But Sarah has other things on her mind.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny is undertaking a drugs trial at Leopard's Den. But de-worming wildebeest isn't Caroline's idea of fun. She hates animals and finds the whole business mind-numbingly boring.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Du Plessis is in a foul mood. It's his 60th birthday and he has no intentions of celebrating it. But the Trevanions have other ideas and Caroline is organising a surprise party.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: All is quiet at Leopard's Den as Sarah, Evan and Olivia gather at the hospital. Danny has been given the all clear to go home. But Du Plessis is still unconscious and seriously ill. Caroline keeps a tender vigil at his bedside.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: Wayne has no money, no passport and a mountain of debt. Homeless and out of options, he's back at the Consulate in Bali with sobering news. But can consular officer, Tom Walter trust his story?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: 56-year-old Michael is living every parent's worst nightmare. His six-year-old son Dylan has been missing for three months now. His ex-wife didn't return him after a routine weekend visit and now he fears that she's trying to smuggle him out of Bali.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 7
programme.desc: Family man Laurie, an offshore oil rigger, is fresh out of jail and claims he's been framed. He's been charged with causing grievous bodily harm after he was involved in a backstreet brawl 12 months ago. Consular officer, Val is on the case.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Aussie expat, Roger arrives at the Embassy after being robbed by a Lady Boy. He says the Lady Boy burst into his hotel room and stole $800 Aussie dollars, along with his drivers licence and international money cards.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 9
programme.desc: Retired construction worker, Ivan, has come to the Embassy with a major financial problem. He purchased a luxury condo in Phuket two years ago, but he still hasn't received the ownership papers from the developer. And it's not looking good.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 10
programme.desc: Mark came to Bali 18 months ago to setup an I.T. business with his Indonesian wife. But unbeknownst to Mark, his passport contains a fake immigration stamp that was issued by a fake immigration agent.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: A leisure helicopter has gone down in Sydney's Royal National Park with a family of four on board, including three year-old Finn. The stakes are always high when children are involved. The rescue crew locates the crash site but can't get too close.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Three surfing mates go missing in dangerous surf. The massive swell threatens to smash them onto the rocks in Sydney's Lurline Bay. The rescue crew is on a search and rescue mission but there's no sign of the surfer boys.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: A monster swell has trapped two teenage girls on the rocks at Sydney's North Head. As high-tide approaches, a daring double-winch rescue is their only option – to stop the teenagers from being swept out to sea.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: A team of amateur scuba divers find themselves in deep trouble when their boat capsizes off Sydney's Botany Bay. The Westpac La Perouse crew spots the distressed divers while on a routine training mission.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 1
programme.desc: Muriwai lifeguard's first rescue of the season is of an unexpected nature and on a remote part of the beach. Lifeguards rush to the aid of a distraught 18-year-old girl whose been sucked into a treacherous hole.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 2
programme.desc: Lifeguards struggle to keep swimmers safe as swift rips sweep them out of the flagged area. But for one boogie boarder it's too late. The young guns are put to the test as a surfer is pounded by huge swells and dragged across jagged rocks.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 3
programme.desc: It's looking like another perfect day for the mounting crowd at Muriwai Beach, but lifeguards soon have a crisis on their hands as a full scale search is mounted for a young boy.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Harley Challenger
programme.desc: Motorcycles introduces you to the lightest power cruiser, the production bike with the biggest cubic capacity worldwide and a phenomenal all-rounder. Ralf Schütze reviews the Ducati Diavel with 162 hp and a weight of a bit more than 200 kg.

programme.title: Motorcycles: iMot Munich
programme.desc: At the IMOT in Munich, one of the major spring fairs, we look for the most important new developments from adventure travel with bikes, high-speed fun on super sports bikes.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Trikes
programme.desc: Anyone who thinks that you can put your feet up and relax, when you drive a trike, is quite mistaken. Motorcycles reviews various trikes for big boys including trikes with up to 200-hp car engines in the rear.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Tiger 800 XC
programme.desc: Motorcycles explores the British way to drive. Of course, that can’t go without talking about the British cult brand Triumph. Our expert Ralf Schütze reviews their Tiger 800 and Tiger 1050.

programme.title: Motorheads: Ferruccio Lamborghini
programme.desc: Portrait of Ferruccio Lamborghini, who originally built tractors, but then moved on to found one of the most famous sports car factories in the world.

programme.title: Motorheads: Ferry Porsche
programme.desc: Portrait of Ferdinand ‘Ferry’ Porsche, the father of the Porsche 911. He started his automobile legacy when he built the Porsche 935 after World War II.

programme.title: Motorheads: Walther Roehrl
programme.desc: Portrait of Walter Röhrl, one of the most famous rally drivers in the world. In this interview he talks about his life, his cars and the manufacturers he raced for.

programme.title: Motorheads: Hans-Joachim Stuck
programme.desc: Portrait of Hans-Joachim Stuck, one of the best race drivers in Germany. He stopped racing after participating in the 2011 24 Hours of Nürburgring.

programme.title: Motorheads: Stephane Peterhansel
programme.desc: Portrait of Stephane Peterhansel, who is a famous rally driver from France and nine-time winner of the Dakar Rallye.

programme.title: Motorheads: Alois Ruf
programme.desc: Portrait of Alois Ruf, who is the founder and owner of the small, but well-known sports car factory ‘Ruf Automobile’ in Germany.

programme.title: Motorheads: Hans Herrmann
programme.desc: Portrait of Hans Herrmann, who was famous Formula 1- and sports car driver in 1950 to 1970. He also won the 24 Hours of Le Mans.

programme.title: Motorheads: Sabine Schmitz
programme.desc: Portrait of Sabine Schmitz, a very successful race driver from Germany and the so-called "Queen of the Nordschleife".

programme.title: Motorheads: Prince Leopold von Bayern
programme.desc: Portrait of Prince Leopold von Bayern, who is a famous race driver from Germany. The Bavarian prince competed in races till 1998 and is now a brand ambassador for BMW.

programme.title: Motorheads: Henry Ford
programme.desc: Portrait of Henry Ford, a man who wanted to improve the world and became a pioneer in the automobile industry by introducing the Model T.

programme.desc: Following Boone's confrontation with Hegel that left him severely injured, he was eliminated by Zo'or. Beckett who was impregnated by Hegel gives birth to a boy who immediately grows up to a man.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Avatus
programme.desc: Da'an looses his contact with the the Taelon Commonality. This causes him to change and Zo'or instructs that Da'an must be killed; because he's now considered a threat.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: A Stitch in Time

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Sleepers
programme.desc: A Jaridian probe lands on Earth and begins sucking energy from the Comonality. The Taelons use humans in a near-death state to keep their connection while Lili and Sandoval try to find out what is draining the energy.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Fissures
programme.desc: When large scale blackouts begin to occur in cities with portals, Taelon technology is blamed. Augur and Liam investigate the death of a portal worker by a strange creature that feeds on energy and is particularly attracted to the Taelons.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Redemption
programme.desc: Siobhan falls while rock climbing. As the others search for her, she dreams that she is on trial for supporting the Taelons. Zo'or questions whether Sandoval's CVI imperative to serve the Taelons has broken down as others are experiencing.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Between Heaven and Hell
programme.desc: Dr. Belman's daughter does human testing on herself with an accelerant that causes her to rapidly evolve. Joshua Doors decides somebody should run against President Thompson in the election, somebody who will stand up to the Taelons.
